 Deepadanda

 Bohurupee?s latest production turns back time to the kingdoms of Pataliputra and Magadh, and the divergent worldviews of surgeons Kumarbhatta Jibak and Sudatta. The social reality of the period is reflected in the conflict of ideologies of an idealist and a realist. Directed by Kumar Roy. 

Catch it at Academy of Fine Arts, 6.30 pm, October 

